BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to 3D Printing
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T170000
UID:69ceb8374dacf581ff861c7b@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In our one-hour introductory class to 3D Printing\, discover t
 he world of 3D printing and learn the step-by-step process behind it. Gain
  an understanding of our 3D printers\, materials used\, and their applicat
 ions. We will also briefly explore popular 3D design softwares\, giving yo
 u an idea of how you can create your very own 3D models. Whether you're a 
 hobbyist\, or interested in incorporating 3D printing into your profession
 al field this class will provide you with foundational knowledge to get st
 arted.\nThis is a drop-in program\n.
LOCATION:Albion\, Digital Innovation Hub
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69ceb8374dacf581ff861c7b
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
