BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Youth Hub: Cuban and Brazilian Drumming - New Date
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T170000
UID:694aec482c65973d00140fb6@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:A\nlively\, hands-on drumming program highlighting two of the 
 most influential countries in world music\, Cuba and Brazil\, both cultura
 lly rich in rhythms and songs. Experience the exciting music of traditiona
 l cultural events like Carnival and community festivals led by ​professi
 onal drummer and percussionist\, Joaquin Hidalgo.\nThis program is part of
  Youth Hub service. Youth Hubs are a welcoming place for teens after schoo
 l and in the summer\, where helpful staff are always available. Free\, nu
 tritious snacks are offered daily. Drop by a branch with a\nYouth Hub\nor
  call the branch to find out more.\nThis event is part of TPL's\nBlack His
 tory and Culture Series\n.
LOCATION:Don Mills\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/694aec482c65973d00140fb6
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Loops\, Swoops and Curlicues Exhibition Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260507T173000
UID:6967f818b0595799c096625f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:How well can you read handwritten items? This free guided tour
  of\nLoops\, Swoops and Curlicues: A legacy of handwritten history\nwill l
 ead your through hundreds of years of handwritten items from TPL Special C
 ollections.\nCome test your decoding skills as we explore several hundred 
 years of handwritten words.\nRegistration is encouraged\, but not required
 . There is space for drop-in guests. Please meet at the entrance to the TD
  Gallery.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on thi
 s form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Librari
 es Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be 
 used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questio
 ns about how the library handles your information can be directed to Answe
 rline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, To
 ronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, TD Gallery\, First Floor of Toronto R
 eference Library
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6967f818b0595799c096625f
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
