BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Discovery Club: Podcasting
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260407T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260407T170000
UID:698a43a781b67dfe32a5537d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wanted to share your stories\, ideas\, or favori
 te topics with the world? In this workshop series\, you’ll work in small
  groups to create your very own short podcast from brainstorming your show
  idea to recording and editing your first episode! Each week\, we’ll exp
 lore a new step in the podcasting process.\nThis program is for ages 9 to 
 12 years old.
LOCATION:Don Mills\, Lower level program room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/698a43a781b67dfe32a5537d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Unfolding Origami Mysteries
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260509T160000
UID:6999f6548d5e2d093360ae4e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special program with Artist Sharon Kawabata as 
 she demonstrates and teaches how to turn origami paper\, into classic ori
 gami pieces: crane\, butterfly\, fish\, etc\, using local animals for insp
 iration and the creation of animal origami as the primary projects. For ch
 ildren ages 6-12 and their caregivers.\nRegistration required. Register on
 line by visiting tpl.ca.
LOCATION:Deer Park\, Room 204
