BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Caribbean Storytime with Yolanda T. Marshall
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260408T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260408T140000
UID:69c429845a2d780f42c4b5f3@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join Yolanda T. Marshall for a Caribbean storytime. We will re
 ad Marching North and will be introduced to the remarkable legacy of Carib
 bean soldiers who served and fought for Canada. Followed by a reading of "
 Brown Girl in the Snow"\, as we sing and dance to a popular Caribbean folk
  song. Followed by a Q & A.\nThis program is for children of all ages & th
 eir caregivers.\nDrop in. Space is limited. Please phone the branch at (41
 6) 393-7686 if you are a teacher hoping to bring a class to this event.\n
 This program will be held in the auditorium.
LOCATION:Parkdale\, Auditorium
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c429845a2d780f42c4b5f3
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
