BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kimbap Making for Teens
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T161500
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260429T171500
UID:69cbe0039057005337d183df@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:TV host and celebrity chef Sang Kim will teach the basics of m
 aking\nKorean-style kimbap\n\, exactly like you see them on your favourite
  K-dramas. Participants will roll and cut kimbap using ingredients prepare
 d by the Chef and eat their own creations. A brief history of kimbap\, its
  differences from the Japanese sushi roll\, and eating etiquette will also
  be shared. Prizes are also awarded for best kimbap creations.\nPlease not
 e: Ingredients include egg and fishcake (which participants do not have t
 o use). This event is for teenagers aged 13-17.
LOCATION:Forest Hill\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cbe0039057005337d183df
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Filmmaking Basics
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T160000
UID:69976fa96724c63d00f3d260@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Recording a video is one thing\, but making movies is a whole 
 other ballgame. In this class we’ll look at how to use the manual settin
 gs on a digital camera to get that “cinematic” look as well as things 
 such as frame rates\, composition\, lighting\, and aspect ratios.\nCamera 
 equipment will be provided for this class. Participants are also welcome t
 o bring their own camera.\nRegistration is required.\nInformation Collecti
 on Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toro
 nto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)
 \, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program regi
 stration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handle
 s your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.
 ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Bagshaw Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69976fa96724c63d00f3d260
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
