UID:69cd5c31db57df04429838d8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join Jasper\, an expressive arts therapist in the 2SLGBTQIA+ c
 ommunity\, for Pride cookie decorating at Toronto Public Library. Celebrat
 e Pride by getting creative and bringing home something sweet!\nJasper Bry
 an (he/they) is a queer expressive arts therapist\, facilitator\, artist\,
  and children's book author and illustrator. He is a leader in Toronto’s
  2SLGBTQIA+ community\, exploring the intersections of art and mental heal
 th to empower everybody. He loves glitter\, arts and crafts\, and rainbows
 !\nYou can access Jasper's picture book\,\nPink & Blue\nat any TPL library
  branch. Pink & Blue is about finding community and being yourself.\nDon
 ’t forget to bring your sweet tooth!\nFood allergy notice: Please be awa
 re that food will be used in this program.  Certain food ingredients may c
 ause allergic reactions in some people.​\nThis program is suitable for c
 hildren ages 6-12. Space is limited. Free tickets will be given out 30 mi
 nutes prior to start time.
LOCATION:Runnymede\, 2nd Floor Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cd5c31db57df04429838d8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
