UID:69b60dc02866a5b488422549@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Python is an open source programming language that is used for
  creating web applications\, web content\, mathematics and system scriptin
 g. In this follow up course we will really start to stretch our legs in Py
 thon\, designing and implementing some simple Object Oriented Programming 
 data structures. Key takeaways will include a working knowledge of Python 
 classes and objects.\nThis class is for beginners but assumes you have a b
 asic understanding of Python or have attended Coding with Python I and II.
 \nRegistration will start 2 weeks before this class. Computers will be pro
 vided.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this f
