BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Youth Hub: Making Comics with Kean Soo
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260501T170000
UID:69c1624b567ba1dd31fe421d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to write and draw comics and graphic novels with the
  award-winning creator of\nJellaby\n! Kean will lead you through the foun
 dations of creating fun\, compelling characters\, plot outlines\, and pull
 ing it all together by laying out and drawing your own comic!\nThis progra
 m is part of Youth Hub service. Youth Hubs are a welcoming place for teens
  after school and in the summer\, where helpful staff are always available
 . Free\, nutritious snacks are offered daily. Drop by a branch with a\nY
 outh Hub\nor call the branch to find out more.
LOCATION:Cedarbrae\, Youth Hub\, 2nd Floor
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1624b567ba1dd31fe421d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FRESH Movie Saturdays
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260411T130000
UID:69c1659f2866a5b48843df08@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn n
 ew skills\, and have fun. Meet new folks\, build connections\, and tell us
  about programs and services you would like to see in the neighbourhood!\n
 Come join us every Saturday for screenings of your favourite movies. In ad
 dition to this\, enjoy cuddles with a therapy dog! Therapy dog Goose visi
 ts Fort York Branch on alternate Saturdays from 11:00AM-12:00PM.\nWe'll b
 e showing the following films:\nApril 4-Honey I Shrunk the Kids\nApril 11-
 Hachi:A Dog's Tale\nApril 18-Zootopia\nApril 25-How to Train Your Dragon(2
 010)\nMay 2-Wonder\nMay 9-Stuart Little\nMay 16-The Jungle Book(1967)\nMay
  23-The Water Horse\nMay 30-Two Brothers\nDrop-ins are welcome.\nThis prog
 ram is in collaboration with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiati
 ve\n.
LOCATION:Fort York\, Urban Living Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1659f2866a5b48843df08
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
