DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260413T193000
UID:69c19214b48451fc3c0ac62d@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Every Monday the Northern District Youth Hub becomes a quieter
  space for teens to study\, work on projects and request help from staff. 
 Grab a snack and work on your homework amongst friends!\nAll teens are wel
 come! Drop-in\, no registration required.\nThis program is part of Youth H
 ub service. Youth Hubs are a welcoming place for teens after school and in
  the summer\, where helpful staff are always available. Free\, nutritious
  snacks are offered daily. Drop by a branch with a\nYouth Hub\nor call th
 e branch to find out more.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Youth Hub (on the second floor)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c19214b48451fc3c0ac62d
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
