BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Accessing the Wisdom of Nature
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260514T123000
UID:69cc31c366c3387a9d05646f@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:The natural world is a source of living wisdom. The stream has
  something to say. So does the wind in the branches\, the moss on a wall\,
  the path a crow takes across the sky. We will talk about traditions acros
 s different cultures that can help us access this wisdom and spend time ou
 tdoors tuning into it. Then we will bring those messages back inside to re
 flect\, illustrate\, and share.\nThe walk will start and end at the Malver
 n Branch. There may be uneven\, unpaved surfaces along the route. Please 
 dress and prepare accordingly for this outdoor program (e.g. gloves/mitten
 s\, hats\, sunscreen\, water\, comfortable shoes). This program takes plac
 e rain or shine. In the event of severe inclement weather\, registrants wi
 ll be notified of an alternative date.\nPlease register online.\nPresented
  by\nClementina Consens\n\, TPL's Spring 2026\nEnvironmentalist in Residen
 ce.\nThe Environmentalist in Residence\nis part of TPL's\nOur Fragile Plan
 et\nprogram series\, supported by Friends of Toronto Public Library\, Sout
 h Chapter.​\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on
  this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Lib
 raries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only
  be used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Que
 stions about how the library handles your information can be directed to A
 nswerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\
 , Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Malvern\, Community Room / Outside
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69cc31c366c3387a9d05646f
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
